The paper deals with information theory and statistical inference, specifically the entropy power inequality and the Fisher information. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which could fall under cs.MS (Mathematical Optimization) and cs.SI (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the connection between entropy power inequality and machine learning, which could potentially fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
